description: The molecule is an octuply-charged cyclic tetrapyrrole anion arising from global deprotonation of the carboxy groups of sirohydrochlorin; major species at pH 7.3. It has a role as a Saccharomyces cerevisiae metabolite and a cofactor. It is a conjugate base of a sirohydrochlorin.

The molecule is an organic sodium salt having 3-ethyl-7-isopropylazulene-1-sulfonate as the counterion. Used for treatment of gastric ulcers. It has a role as an anti-ulcer drug and a thromboxane A2 antagonist. It is an organosulfonate salt and an organic sodium salt. It contains an egualen(1-).
